description: Number of equivalence classes of Boolean functions of n variables under action of LSD(n,2).
comments: Linear self-dual group LSD(n,2) is group of n X n non-singular matrices over GF(2) with odd number of units in each row.
references: I. Strazdins, Universal affine classification of Boolean functions, Acta Applic. Math. 46 (1997), 147-167.
V. Jovovic, The cycle index polynomials of some classical groups, Belgrade, 1995, unpublished.
links: Index entries for sequences related to Boolean functions
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
